<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Vertex medially transversely impressed, longer medially than next to eyes, about 
<number box="[1225,1240,306,332]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
times as broad between eyes as median length; anterior margin with 
<number box="[793,808,345,371]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="4.0">4</number>
transverse carinae dorsad of ocelli, stem of ecdysial line well-developed. Face in profile flat, with 
<number box="[721,736,384,410]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
transverse carinae ventrad of ocelli, rest shagreen. Ocelli placed 
<number box="[236,251,422,448]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="2.0">2</number>
times own diameter away from adjacent eye. Pronotum in profile slightly convex, anterior margin convex. Scutellum, flat. 
<collectingCountry box="[437,496,461,487]" name="India" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Hind</collectingCountry>
basitarsus with 
<number box="[685,700,461,487]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="3.0">3</number>
platellae on apical transverse row.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis box="[198,370,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Male pygophore conically rounded caudo-dorsally, with several stout setae in caudal half, without appendages or oblique ridge. Subgenital plate triangular with caudal appendage, with few marginal slender short setae, inner margin straight in proximal half. Style stout, without subapical lobe, caudally truncate, inner angle bluntly mesally produced, surface with transverse and oblique rugae. Aedeagus with well-developed broad plate at base preceding dorsal apodeme, latter bearing lateral sinuate, blade-like process with serrated distal margin in ventral view (arrowed in 
<figureCitation box="[841,1013,693,719]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 13" captionStartId="2.[151,258,1899,1920]" captionTargetBox="[182,1436,188,1898]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,156,1901]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 13. Bhatia radhamaniae sp. nov. 1. Head and thorax, dorsal view; 2. Head and thorax, profile; 3. Face; 4. Forewing, 5. Male pygophore, lateral view; 6. Subgenital plate; 7. Male style; 8. Connective; 9. Aedeagus, lateral view; 10. Aedeagus, ventral view; 11. Female seventh sternite, ventral view; 12. Second pair of valvula, left lateral view; 13. Magnified view of teeth on second pair of valvula, left lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190679/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
Figs 
<number box="[902,917,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="9.0">9</number>
and 
<number box="[979,1013,693,719]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
); shaft cylindrical, half as long as posterior processes, with large gonopore opening on posterior surface apically; with pair of posterior long caudally diverging slender processes arising near base of shaft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis box="[198,398,809,834]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Female genitalia</emphasis>
: Seventh sternum broader than long, medially produced into bilobed projection. Second pair of valvulae with anterior tubercle, cutting edge 
<number box="[822,862,848,874]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" value="0.4">0.4</number>
as long as total length, teeth prominent with crenulations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,1222]" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis box="[198,368,925,950]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="50">Measurements</emphasis>
: Male 
<quantity box="[454,597,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.4" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="6.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="6.4" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="6.1">6.1–6.7 mm</quantity>
long and 2.0– 
<quantity box="[771,861,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="2.1">2.1 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes. Female 
<quantity box="[1181,1324,925,951]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="8.3" metricValueMin="8.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="8.25" valueMax="8.3" valueMin="8.2">8.2–8.3 mm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[151,241,964,990]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="50" unit="mm" value="2.3">2.3 mm</quantity>
wide across eyes.
</paragraph>
